(9, 1, '2020-02-12 00:40:55', '2020-02-12 00:40:55', '<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://img.apksum.com/32/com.pagerduty.android/5.81/icon.png\" alt=\"Image result for pagerduty icon\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Save On Clouds can send notifications to PagerDuty via <em>Wormly Webhooks</em> plugin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have not installed the Wormly Webhooks integration upon creating your PagerDuty account, you can install it via Configuration / Integrations menu within your PagerDuty dashboard.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Notifications will be sent to a Service via an associated Integration. In order to activate the Wormly Webhook on a service, go to the Service Directory (/service-directory) and click on the name of an existing Service.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each Service can entail one or more integrations. In order to receive notifications from Save On Clouds, add a new integration and from the drop-down list, choose Wormly Webhooks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the integration is added successfully by clicking on \"Add Integration\" , Pager Duty will provide you with an Integration Url:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":8,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-default\"><img src=\"https://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/image-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Integration Url is what you need to put in your Save On Cloud\'s \"Notification\" page (under your profile). </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Simply go to your profile and choose \"Notifications\". Then add a notification of type PagerDuty and in the address field, paste the Integration URL that you have been given by PagerDuty.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Integration with PagerDuty', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-12 00:40:55', '2020-02-12 00:40:55', '', 5, 'https://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(10, 1, '2020-04-26 20:47:45', '2020-04-26 20:47:45', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Save On Clouds can send notifications to Google Chat Rooms via Webhooks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to receive notifications, firstly you need to create a room.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":11,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the room is created, make sure you are in the room. Then expand the drop-down menu on the top of the screen and click on \"Configure Webhooks\" option.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":13,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/image-5.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Provide a name and click on Save.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":14,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/image-6.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-14\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you click on the Save button, Google Chat will provide you with a Webhook address. This URL is what you need to place in Save On Clouds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":15,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/image-7.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-15\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy the provided link/URL to the clipboard, and go back to your profile page Save On Clouds. In the Notifications tab, add a Google Chat notification channel and paste the link in the Address box.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Integration with Google Chat Hangout', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'integration-with-google-chat-hangout', '', '', '2020-04-26 20:47:45', '2020-04-26 20:47:45', '', 0, 'http://saveoncloudsblog.cloud/?p=10', 0, 'post', '', 0),
