create an IAM role.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":74,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://info.saveonclouds.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image-18.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-74\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And finally, click on Create Stack.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Creating the stack will take about one to two minutes. Wait until you see the green \"Creation Completed\" status.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the Cloud Formation Stack is created, go to \"<strong>Outputs</strong>\" tab, where you can see the ARN of the IAM role that has just been created.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Click the value (which begins with arn:aws:) to the ClipBoard.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":75,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://info.saveonclouds.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image-19-1024x175.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-75\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now go back to Save On Clouds, and:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Enter a name for your Cloud Account.</li><li>Paste the ARN in the \"IAM Role Arn\" box.</li><li>Click on Test Connection button.</li><li>Click on Create Account button.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You are done!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you add an account, Save On Clouds begins to fetch your cloud resources immediately. This will take around 30 seconds to 1 minutes depending on the number of resources you have (and how fast AWS responds!).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wait for a minute then head to \"Cloud Resources\" page to view and mange your cloud resources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Happy saving!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Adding an AWS Cloud Account', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '68-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-12 01:57:54', '2020-04-12 01:57:54', '', 68, 'https://info.saveonclouds.com/68-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(77, 1, '2020-04-12 08:44:49', '2020-04-12 08:44:49', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Obviously, in order to optimise the utilization of your cloud resources you need to connect to your account in the relevant cloud provider, such as AWS or Azure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We call these connections as \"Cloud Accounts\". A cloud account is essentially a set of credentials that you provide to Save On Clouds so that the system can connect to and manage your resources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Save On Clouds uses the minimum access rights so you will not need to worry about the security of your cloud account. We only obtain a temporary and short-lived token to access to your cloud provider.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the moment Save On Clouds can connect to the below cloud providers:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Amazon Web Services</li><li>Microsoft Azure</li><li>Google Cloud Platform</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To begin connecting to your cloud provider, simply click on the relevant button on the top of the page.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":78,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://info.saveonclouds.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image-20.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-78\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Clicking on any of these buttons will open a dialog box which lets you enter your credentials.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You will find a help (a question mark) button on the top right corner of the window. It is highly advised that you click on this button and read the documentation before you proceed. This is important because, especially for MS Azure and Google Cloud Platform, if you do not configure your permissions correctly, Save On Clouds will not be able to fetch your cloud resources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":79,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://info.saveonclouds.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image-21.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-79\"/><figcaption>The ? button provides plenty of information about connecting to your cloud provider.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Cloud Accounts', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cloud-accounts', '', '', '2020-04-12 08:45:05', '2020-04-12 08:45:05', '', 0, 'http://info.saveonclouds.com/?p=77', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(78, 1, '2020-04-12 08:41:43', '2020-04-12 08:41:43', '', 'image-20', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'image-20', '', '', '2020-04-12 08:41:43', '2020-04-12 08:41:43', '', 77, 'http://info.saveonclouds.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image-20.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
