(127, 1, '2020-04-27 00:01:09', '2020-04-27 00:01:09', '<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Google Hangouts integration is available to G-Suite users only. Personal accounts do not have access to Webhooks feature in Google Hangout chat.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To setup Google Hangouts webhooks you have to install the Google Hangouts extension on Google Chrome.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":125,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://info.saveonclouds.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image-49-1024x214.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-125\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the extension is installed, the Google Hangouts form will appear on the screen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Click on \"New Conversation\" then click on \"New Group\" if you do not already have a Group. Provide a name and click on Save. For example, create a Group and call it \"DevOps Team\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":126,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://info.saveonclouds.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image-50.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-126\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'cancel', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '113-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-27 00:01:09', '2020-04-27 00:01:09', '', 113, 'https://info.saveonclouds.com/113-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(128, 1, '2020-04-27 00:09:24', '2020-04-27 00:09:24', '<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-rounded\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://banner2.cleanpng.com/20180506/vhw/kisspng-webhook-slack-application-programming-interface-5aef6ba8145e52.2061982515256401040834.jpg\" alt=\"Pink Circle png download - 1600*1600 - Free Transparent Webhook ...\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Generic Web-Hook integration will enable you to send notifications to virtually unlimited number and types of applications, as long as they support incoming web hooks. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using Web Hooks you can also initiate automation processes using third-party systems such as <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://zapier.com\" target=\"_blank\">Zapier</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All Web Hooks are accessible via a Service URL. This is how applications such as Slack, MS Teams and Google Hangouts are able to receive notifications from Save On Clouds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To integrate with a generic Web Hook, please refer to the documentation of your specific application and find out how Incoming Web-hooks are configured.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the incoming webhook is configured in your applciation, head back to Save On Clouds and add a new notification channel of type \"WebHook\". Then put your Webhook Url in the Endpoint box and your channels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No further configuration is required apart from deciding what kinds of alerts you would like to receive. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Integration with Generic Web Hook', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '113-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-27 00:09:24', '2020-04-27 00:09:24', '', 113, 'https://info.saveonclouds.com/113-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
